{%- comment -%}
  LE FIGUE — LE FIGUE Society. Ported from le-figue-society.html.
  Design's own masthead stripped; theme header/footer wrap it. ALWAYS DARK
  (2026-07-07, user request): the prefers-color-scheme media wrappers were
  removed so the dark palette applies unconditionally in every viewer/editor.
  CSS scoped under .lf-society. Internal links repointed to /pages/*.
{%- endcomment -%}

<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Cormorant+Garamond:ital,wght@0,400;0,500;0,600;1,400;1,500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<link rel="stylesheet" crossorigin href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/orioncactus/pretendard@v1.3.9/dist/web/variable/pretendardvariable.min.css">

<div class="lf-society">
<!-- HERO -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="seal-bg" id="seal-bg"></div>
    <div class="inner wrap">
      <div class="ov">Private Client Program</div>
      <h1>Le Figue Society</h1>
      <div class="sub">A society, not a sale.</div>
      <p>LE FIGUE SOCIETY is our private circle, for those who return, collect, and slowly compose a language of jewelry that is their own. Membership is not earned by spending. It is a relationship that opens gently, with House Credits that find their way back to you, member pricing kept quiet, private access, and personal services that deepen the longer you stay with us.</p>
      <button class="scrolldown" onclick="document.getElementById('join').scrollIntoView()">Enter the society</button>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="sep"></div>

  <!-- MANIFESTO + PILLARS -->
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="manifesto">
      <div class="ov">The idea</div>
      <h2>Not a sale. A relationship.</h2>
      <p>We do not follow the rhythm of ordinary sales. Every purchase brings you closer to the next tier, and every tier opens a quieter, more personal way to experience LE FIGUE.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="pillars">
      <div class="pillar"><div class="pi"></div><div class="pn">House Credits</div><div class="pd">A quiet share of every purchase returns to you as House Credits, worth two dollars for every hundred, kept for whatever you discover next.</div></div>
      <div class="pillar"><div class="pi"></div><div class="pn">Member Pricing</div><div class="pd">A quieter price, applied at checkout. No codes, and no season to wait for.</div></div>
      <div class="pillar"><div class="pi"></div><div class="pn">Private Access</div><div class="pd">Previews, appointments, and styling that open as your relationship with the society deepens.</div></div>
    </div>

    <div class="how">
      <div class="ov">How it works</div>
      <p>Seven tiers, each one a step further into the society. You move with what you collect, never with a sale.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- TIER EXPLORER -->
    <div class="tiers-wrap">
      <div class="tiers-head"><div class="ov">The Tiers</div><h2>Seven ways into the society</h2>
        <div class="tier-toggle"><button class="on" data-v="explore">Explore</button><button data-v="compare">Compare</button></div>
      </div>
      <div id="explore-view"><div class="explorer">
        <div class="rail" id="rail"></div>
        <div class="tier-detail" id="tier-detail"></div>
      </div></div>
      <div id="compare-view"></div>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <div class="faq">
      <div class="faq-head"><div class="ov">FAQ</div><h2>A few questions</h2></div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q">Can I share or transfer my membership?<span class="faq-ic">+</span></button><div class="faq-a"><p>Membership is personal. Your tier, House Credits, and member pricing belong to you alone. They cannot be transferred, gifted, or used by anyone else on your behalf.</p></div></div>
        <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q">What happens if I leave and rejoin?<span class="faq-ic">+</span></button><div class="faq-a"><p>You are always welcome back, though a new membership begins again at The Guest. A previous tier is not restored, as each tier is earned through the relationship as it grows.</p></div></div>
        <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q">Does membership work online and in store?<span class="faq-ic">+</span></button><div class="faq-a"><p>Yes. Your tier, House Credits, and member pricing are recognized the same way online and at our locations.</p></div></div>
        <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q">Does member pricing combine with other prices?<span class="faq-ic">+</span></button><div class="faq-a"><p>Member pricing applies to eligible full price pieces. It does not stack on prices that are already composed at a special rate, such as pairings at Set 15% or pieces offered on pre-order.</p></div></div>
        <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q">Which pieces are eligible?<span class="faq-ic">+</span></button><div class="faq-a"><p>Most full price pieces are eligible. Fine jewelry, bespoke orders, repairs, special collaborations, limited editions, gift cards, taxes, shipping, and selected designer pieces may not be. We may refine tier benefits, eligibility, and terms as the society evolves.</p></div></div>
        <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q">How do I earn House Credits?<span class="faq-ic">+</span></button><div class="faq-a"><p>House Credits are the currency of the society, valued at one hundred credits to two dollars. You earn them as a share of each eligible purchase, from one percent at The Guest rising to two and a half percent at the highest tiers, and through welcome, birthday, anniversary, and referral rewards. When you enter a higher tier directly, that tier's welcome credits are granted once on entry, and earlier tier credits are not added retroactively.</p></div></div>
        <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q">How do I use my House Credits?<span class="faq-ic">+</span></button><div class="faq-a"><p>Your House Credits are applied at checkout, the same way online and in store, at one hundred credits to two dollars. They may be used once your balance reaches five hundred credits, which is ten dollars, and in increments of one hundred above that. Eligibility is shown at checkout.</p></div></div>
      </div>
      <div style="text-align:center;margin-top:34px"><a href="/pages/society-terms" style="font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.16em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--accent);border-bottom:1px solid var(--gold);padding-bottom:3px;text-decoration:none">Read the full Society terms &rarr;</a></div>
    </div>


  </div>

  <!-- JOIN -->
  <section class="join" id="join">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="seal" id="join-seal"></div>
      <div class="ov">Membership</div>
      <h2>Enter the society</h2>
      <p class="lede">Membership begins the moment you join. The Guest receives 250 House Credits, and the society opens from there.</p>

      <div class="join-card" id="join-card">
        <div class="grid2">
          <div class="field"><label>First name</label><input id="fn" autocomplete="given-name"></div>
          <div class="field"><label>Last name</label><input id="ln" autocomplete="family-name"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="field full"><label>Email</label><input id="em" type="email" autocomplete="email"></div>
        <div class="grid2">
          <div class="field"><label>Password</label><input id="pw" type="password" autocomplete="new-password"></div>
          <div class="field"><label>Confirm password</label><input id="pw2" type="password" autocomplete="new-password"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="field full"><label>Birthday month <span class="opt">for your birthday House Credits</span></label>
          <select id="bm">
            <option value="">Prefer not to say</option>
            <option>January</option><option>February</option><option>March</option><option>April</option>
            <option>May</option><option>June</option><option>July</option><option>August</option>
            <option>September</option><option>October</option><option>November</option><option>December</option>
          </select>
        </div>
        <label class="consent"><input type="checkbox" id="cs" checked> I would like to receive previews, appointments, and the occasional note from the society.</label>
        <button class="join-cta" id="join-cta">Enter the society</button>
        <div class="err-msg" id="err"></div>
        <p class="join-fine">By joining you become a member of LE FIGUE SOCIETY at The Guest. You may leave the society at any time.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="join-done" id="join-done" hidden>
        <div class="seal" id="done-seal"></div>
        <h3>Welcome to the society</h3>
        <p id="done-msg"></p>
        <div class="credits">250 House Credits are yours.</div>
        <a class="join-cta" href="/pages/my-status" style="display:inline-block;text-decoration:none;max-width:300px;margin:26px auto 0">Enter your Society &rarr;</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="refer-min"><div class="wrap"><div class="rm-inner">
    <div class="rm-mark"></div>
    <div class="rm-ov">Bring a friend</div>
    <p class="rm-line">When someone you invite joins, <span class="amt">$50 in House Credits</span> arrives for you both.</p>
    <div class="rm-link"><input id="ref-link" readonly value="lefigue.com/society/invite"><button id="ref-copy">Copy</button></div>
    <p class="rm-fine">Credited once they join and make a first eligible purchase.</p>
  </div></div></section>

  <div class="figline"><span class="mark">·&nbsp;·&nbsp;·</span><p>A society is not a sale. It is a place you are known.</p></div>
</div>

